Grab Table set

rr library(rvest) # load dplyr library(dplyr) # set the page code as a vector pages <- c(1 ,41, 81, 121, 161, 201, 241) # seq(from=1, 241, by=40) # create a vector for url for (i in pages){ if (i >= 2) { url <- append(url, sprintf(://www.espn.com/nba/statistics/player//stat/scoring-per-game/sort/avgPoints/count/%s, i))}else{ url <- sprintf(://www.espn.com/nba/statistics/player//stat/scoring-per-game/sort/avgPoints/count/%s, i)} } # for loop to sort through pages for (num in 1:7){ nba_player_data <- read_html(url[num]) %>% # url1 was created before for loop. html_nodes(.tablehead) %>% html_table(header=TRUE) # get raw dataframe and set to variable nba_player_data <- nba_player_data[[1]] # drops column
nba_player_data <- nba_player_data[, -c(1)] # drops row with  in it to remove headers from rows nba_player_data <- nba_player_data[!(nba_player_data$PLAYER==), ] # write cleaned_data to a csv file write.csv(nba_player_data, file=sprintf(_%s.csv, num)) }
